  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Around the World — Global Editions","description":"Explore how Scrabble adapts to 30+ languages worldwide — from French accent tiles to Welsh double-letter tiles, Arabic right-to-left boards, and radically different tile distributions per language.","datePublished":"2026-06-14","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-around-the-world"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many languages is Scrabble available in?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Scrabble is officially produced in over 30 languages, including French, German, Spanish, Italian, Dutch, Arabic, Malay, Welsh, Hebrew, Greek, and many more. Each edition has a unique tile distribution calculated from that language's letter frequency, and some editions include special characters like accented letters or multi-letter tiles."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Welsh Scrabble have different tiles than English?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Welsh Scrabble treats digraphs like LL, CH, DD, FF, NG, PH, RH, and TH as single tiles because they represent single sounds in Welsh. This means the Welsh set has tiles with two printed letters that count as one tile on the board, fundamentally changing rack management and word formation."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is Scrabble played in Arabic?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Arabic Scrabble is played right-to-left, matching the natural direction of Arabic script. The board layout is mirrored, and the tile set includes all 28 Arabic letters. Since Arabic is written without most vowels in everyday text, the game dynamics differ significantly from English — consonant management becomes more critical than vowel balance."}}]})} />
